                  <persName id="t18140914-159-person1387">
                  JOHN 
                  BREES
               <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1387" type="surname" value="BREES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1387" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1387" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lost my property on the 8th of August. I was waiting to get into my lodgings in <placeName id="t18140914-159-crimeloc891">Golden-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18140914-159-crimeloc891" type="placeName" value="Golden-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18140914-159-crimeloc891" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18140914-159-off889 t18140914-159-crimeloc891"></join>. I thought the young man heard me; he did not. It was a quarter past eleven in the evening. I was perfectly sober. I was tired. I fell asleep on the step on the opposite side of the way; the prisoner came past, and took off my shoes. I awoke when he took off the last shoe. I held the prisoner until the watchman came to my assistance.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18140914-159-person1388">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MONDAY
               <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1388" type="surname" value="MONDAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1388" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140914-159-person1388" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of St. Luke's. About a quarter past eleven, I was walking to and fro. I heard the prisoner sing out watchman. I knew his voice. I ran up Golden-lane, and saw the prosecutor; I said, what do you call me for; he said, this man has taken my shoes. The prisoner said, he had not the shoes. The prosecutor said, you gave them to your comrade.</p>
